channel.title: [PI] Compile Error Help? [PI]
channel.description:
Hey guys,
I added Dungeoneering, but I get the error 'symbol not found' at all of those things:
[code]src\server\model\shops\ShopAssistant.java:449: error: method handleOtherShop in class ShopAssistant cannot be applied to given types; handleOtherShop(itemID, amount, fromSlot); ^ required: int found: int,int,int reason: actual and formal argument lists differ in length src\server\model\players\PlayerAssistant.java:1570: error: cannot find symbol if (Dungeoneering.Dung(c)) { ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class PlayerAssistant src\server\model\players\PlayerAssistant.java:1627: error: cannot find symbol if (Dungeoneering.Dung(c)) { ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class PlayerAssistant src\server\model\players\PlayerAssistant.java:1700: error: cannot find symbol if (Dungeoneering.Dung(c)) { ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class PlayerAssistant src\server\model\npcs\NPCHandler.java:1840: error: cannot find symbol if (Dungeoneering.isDungNpc(npcType)) { ^ symbol: variable npcType location: class NPCHandler src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:833: error: cannot find sy mbol Dungeoneering.startFloor1(c); ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class ClickingButtons src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:990: error: cannot find sy mbol Dungeoneering.redostartfloor1(c); ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class ClickingButtons src\server\model\players\packets\ClickingButtons.java:1026: error: cannot find s ymbol Dungeoneering.leaveDung(c); ^ symbol: variable Dungeoneering location: class ClickingButtons Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 8 errors Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
What is wrong? 'cuz I don't get it.
Thanks in advance, Mthijs3.

item.title: [PI] Compile Error Help? [PI]
item.dc:creator: @TheProdigy TheProdigy
item.description:
@TheProdigy wrote:

First error is due to the handleOtherShop method needing only one parameter. Edit it so it fits or create a new method for the 3 parameters.

Second error is due to the methods and variables not being static. I would recommend casting them through inheritance though.
Read about that here: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/IandI/subclasses.html
